place.name: TILNEY ST LAWRENCE
place.gazetteerText: TILNEY-ST. LAWRENCE, a parish, with a village, in the district of Wisbeach and county of Norfolk; 3½ miles S of Terrington r. station, and 6 SW of Lynn. Post town, Lynn. Acres, 3,366. Real property, £7,995. Pop., 855. Houses, 112. The property is much sub-divided. The manor belongs to the Queen. The living is a vicarage, annexed to T.-All-Saints. The church was restored in 1846. There are three Primitive Methodist chapels, and charities £22. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
